    longDescription: "Date Difference Calculator measures the span between two dates in days, weeks, months, and related units for project plans, visa timelines, invoice terms, and school calendars. Project managers count working windows; freelancers compute late fees; students pace study schedules between milestones. Pick a start and end date, calculate the difference, and interpret inclusive versus exclusive counts carefully (overnight hotel nights often differ from “number of calendar dates listed”). All math stays in the browser so confidential deal timelines never leave your device. When multiple time zones complicate “the same day,” combine with a timezone converter so both parties agree which calendar date applies. Align start-of-day assumptions when contracts use “business days” rather than calendar days. Export the counted span into project trackers as a duration field for Gantt charts.",
